CHID-Fi can extract 3D hand keypoints behind occlusions (b-d). Note that the wrist and the position of the hand are shown here only as an example. In the actual experiment, the hand can be fully occluded and its position can vary. Drawn outlines here are for illustration purposes only. factors: it requires Line-of-Sight (LoS) [10,18] and certain lighting conditions [4, 46], it is prone to background clutter [17,40], and is challenged by privacy concerns [1,3]. Motivated by these shortcomings, non-optical ...},
